StringMaps - Class in <Unnamed>
StringMaps functions to search through all of the files provided to its constructor, breaking each txt file into string sequences of length six and storing these sequences in a list unique for each file, and adding each unique sequence to a hashmap.
StringMaps(List<File>, int, int) - Constructor for class StringMaps
Each file is assigned a StringMaps.FileSequences object that stores all StringMaps.sequenceSize sequences and uID (file name) and the hashmap of all sequences is generated
